class Solution {
    public int leastOpsExpressTarget(int x, int target) {
        if (x == target) return 0;
        if (x > target) return Math.min(2, target);
        long cur = x;
        int count = 0;
        while (cur < target) {
            cur *= x;
            count++;
        }
        if (cur == target) return count;
        long pre = cur / x;
        long diff1 = cur - target;
        long diff2 = target - pre;
        int res1 = count + (int) Math.ceil((double) diff1 / x);
        int res2 = count - 1 + (int) Math.ceil((double) diff2 / x);
        return Math.min(res1, res2);
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log(target)/log(x))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution uses a greedy approach, iteratively multiplying x until it exceeds the target, then adjusting the expression to get as close to the target as possible with the least number of operations.
